	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I bumped into a weird problem , my built-in video card of g41mt-es2l mother board , is read 1024mb on XP and 64mb on Win 7 64 or 32 bit , however 1024 is the actual capacity.....<br />I don't know how win 7 reads it too low like this!!!!!!!!!and I can't find any option on bios enables me to increase it from 64mb to any capacity...<br />anyone here ever encountered or fixed a problem like this?and how?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
